        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=77810&TOPIC_ID=9498&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=+&Topic_Title=Hitpoints+and+Mana&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Okay, <BR>Basic mediatate at level 60 gives you 25 mana per tick. (without AA points into mental clarity) <BR>Basic regeneration for most classes is 6 hp a tick while sitting, and 18 hp a tick for Iksars.  (without AA points into regen or regen items)</P><P>add to that Demi Lich<BR>Increase Mana by 31 a tick.<BR>Decrease Hit Points by 48 a tick.</P><P>That gives you 56 mana every tick while sitting, and reduces 42 hitpoints a tick while sitting (30 hitpoints a tick for iksars).</P><P>Mathematically, the amount of hitpoints you need to go from zero mana, to max mana is equal to:</P><P>Hitpoints = Manapool*(Hp loss rate)/(Mana gain rate)</P><P>Demi Lich results:<BR>Hitpoints = Manapool*0.75<BR>Hitpoints = Manapool*0.54 (for iksars)</P><P>Regular Lich results:<BR>Hitpoints = Manapool*0.55<BR>Hitpoints = Manapool*0.29 (for iksars)</P><P>So if you have 3000 mana, your ideal hp amount is 2250hp for Demi Lich, and 1650hp if you're using regular lich, (1620hp and 870hp for iksars).  </P><P>Of course this is in a perfect system where the necro doesn't get damaged and is always sitting.  In practice you are going to get hit by mobs, spells, and AOE's and should have a larger hitpoint pool, by how much is up to you guys. <img src=icon_smile_big.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P><IMG BORDER=0 ALIGN="CENTER" WIDTH=180 HEIGHT=140 SRC="http://www3.telus.net/xarkxem/blackmage.jpg" </><BR><br><BR>Valishar Sa`Veera<BR>60th Level Witchy Warlock<BR>-Acropolis-<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

